Been riding for near 10 years now. I only experienced 1 driver that purposefully tried to wreck me for no reason. All the other times were either the driver not paying attention (changing lanes without looking, pulling out without looking, etc) or me not paying attention (riding in their blind spot without realizing it, changing lanes without looking, etc). For those people arguing over whether this brown snake is venomous or not. It is important that you realise there are more than one type of Brown snake. 

There is the little brown snake, found in the United States. This snake is harmless and Non venomous. 

There is then the Eastern Brown Snake, which is found in Australia, Papua New Guinea, and Indonesia. Now this snake is the one seen in the video and it is the second most venomous land snake in the world. 

There is then also the Australian Mulga aka The King Brown Snake. This snake is also venomous however not as dangerous as the Eastern Brown Snake. It is also much larger. 

There is even a Short Stub Nose brown snake found in south western Australia, however that is not the type seen in the video. 

The snake in the video is dangerous.

I worked at the Tulsa Zoo as night security...first day on the job my supervisor walks me around the zoo and shows me the doors I need to check, we get to the Kodiak Bear Enclosure where I meet Yukon...the 1400 pound bear...John says...now..whatever you do..dont try and pet this bear!...I laughed John to scorn...I told him he wouldnt have to worry as that would be the stupidest thing in the world and I would never think of doing it in a million years...John just looked at me with a blank stare and said nothing...4 months later...Yukon and I are friends...He likes me...he waits for me to come and check the locks on his enclosure and we talk..well..I talk..he just stares at me through the food port and pants like a cute little puppy...his muzzle is very similar to a dogs muzzle..and that fateful night when I could tell...Yukon wanted me to scratch his nose...he poked it out of the food port so I could rub it and scratch it...without thinking...I extended my hand out to scratch his furry muzzle , I was even speaking to him as if he was an adorable puppy...and in an instant...I could feel his hot breath and see his razor sharp teeth snap at my fingers...it happened so fast that the hairs on the back of my neck stood straight up at attention..I snatched my hand back just in time to avoid it being amputated. Johns words came echoing back to my mind...Whatever you do..dont try and pet this bear...I asked john about the night guard I was replacing...he had lost 3 fingers to Yukon...True Story...Bears look harmless and fuzzy and full of love...but they are definitely dangerous...even when you think they are your friends...Yukon set me up..biding his time...he wanted some fingers...and mine were on the menu...RIP Yukon...I hope he is getting lots of fingers in Bear heaven...
